Description: Raised and flaring rim sherd and base (mended from two fragments) of Corinthian pottery plate; groove on top of rim near edge; double moulding at edge of underside; exterior: traces of glaze on edge of rim; on top of rim band of in outline, with, to the inside, band of 'z' between pairs of lines, all very worn.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.265) (phase 3)
